# iTrialSpace

**Synthetic Imaging Clinical Trial Engine for lung CT AI evaluation.**

> ⚠️ License is not yet finalized — see [`LICENSE`](LICENSE). Do not redistribute until confirmed.

iTrialSpace turns medical-imaging AI evaluation from *"find more data"* into *"specify the
data you need."* It harmonizes **13,140 nodule profiles** from **7 public lung CT datasets**,
generates virtual clinical-trial cohorts across **13 trial modes**, inserts donor nodule masks
into real host anatomy, synthesizes CT volumes with a ControlNet-conditioned rectified-flow
diffusion model (**NodMAISI**), and evaluates **CADe/CADx** detectors and **vision-language
models** under systematically controlled conditions.

## Why

Public lung-screening datasets are narrow (NLST = heavy smokers, LUNA16 has no malignancy
labels, NSCLC-Radiomics = only large cancers), so AI models get tested on data that
under-represents where they fail. iTrialSpace lets you declare a cohort by its *statistical
properties* (prevalence, size distribution, lobe distribution, demographics) and manufactures
anatomically grounded synthetic CTs to match — enabling controlled, one-variable-at-a-time
experiments impossible with fixed retrospective datasets.

## Architecture

```
itrialspace      →  trials        →  mask_inserter  →  synthesis     →  evaluation
(nodule index)      (manifests)      (mask paste)      (NodMAISI CT)    (CADe/CADx/VLM)
   │
   ├─ nodulemap   (graph viz)
   └─ retriever   (faceted search)
```

See [docs/architecture.md](docs/architecture.md) for the full component map.

## Quickstart

```bash
# 1. Environment
conda env create -f environment.yml && conda activate itrialspace

# 2. Install (pick the extras you need — see Install matrix below)
pip install -e ".[imaging,web]"

# 3. Configure paths
cp .env.example .env      # edit ITRIALSPACE_DATA_DIR etc.

# 4. Run unit tests (no external data required)
pytest -m "not full_volume"

# 5. Build the nodule index and print stats (requires profile CSVs — see docs/data.md)
its index stats
```

## Install matrix

| Extra | Installs | For |
|-------|----------|-----|
| *(base)* | pandas, numpy, pyyaml | Index, query, trial planning |
| `imaging` | nibabel, scipy, SimpleITK | Mask insertion, NIfTI handling |
| `web` | fastapi, streamlit, faiss, umap | NoduleMap + Retriever UIs |
| `synthesis` | monai, (torch) | NodMAISI CT synthesis* |
| `vlm` | transformers, open_clip | VLM evaluation* |
| `eval` | monai, scikit-learn | CADe/CADx evaluation** |
| `dev` | pytest, ruff, black, pre-commit | Development |
| `all` | imaging + web + vlm + dev | Everything bundled |

\* torch is platform-specific — see [docs/installation.md](docs/installation.md).
\*\* also needs **external** models/repos — see [docs/evaluation_external_dependencies.md](docs/evaluation_external_dependencies.md).

## Console commands

| Command | Does |
|---------|------|
| `its` | Umbrella CLI (index, query, info) |
| `its-insert` | Insert nodule masks from a cohort manifest |
| `its-trials` | Generate cohort manifests for the 13 trial modes |
| `its-nodulemap` | Launch the NoduleMap graph-visualization server |
| `its-retriever` | Launch the Retriever search API + UI |

